data.description: **Offering $12,000 towards 2-1 buydown, down payment, or price reduction!** Experience the charm of this captivating single-story residence nestled in the sought-after Parke-Grandview Hills Subdivision. This 4-bedroom, 2.5-bathroom haven offers a rare blend of spaciousness and light that's hard to find.  Upon entry, a welcoming ambiance envelops you, with a formal living room and dining area on your right. Across lies one of three guest bedrooms, presently utilized as an office, accompanied by a convenient half bathroom. Moving forward, a hallway leads to the primary suite on the left and two additional guest bedrooms with a Jack and Jill bathroom on the right.  The rear of the house unveils a spacious family room adorned with a fireplace, complemented by an informal dining area and a generously sized kitchen. Recent updates include fresh interior painting and newly replaced carpets, enhancing the overall appeal of the home. Not to mention, a newer AC unit adds to the lower operating costs of the property.  Discover the convenience of exemplary schools within close proximity, making this neighborhood highly coveted. The walking distance to the grade school and the nearby highly-ranked Vandergrift high school adds to the appeal.  Embrace the elegance of the property surrounded by a canopy of trees, offering both shade and scenic beauty. The partially fenced backyard features a deck and a flat, usable yard, while the community amenities of Parke elevate your living experience, boasting a pool, playground, sports courts, and scenic walking/jogging trails.  Enjoy the convenience of being near Four Points, a myriad of restaurants, HEB, shopping centers, Lake Travis, and more, all adding to the appeal and convenience of this remarkable home.
